INSERT INTO `#__content`  VALUES ('7', '47', 'About PLUG', 'about-plug', '<p>Founded in 1994, the Philippine Linux Users\' Group (PLUG) is a non-stock, non-profit organization that advocates for the adoption of the GNU/Linux operating system and free and open source software in the Philippines. Composed entirely of volunteers from many sectors of society such as businesses, the academe, government, medical sciences and other non-government organizations, PLUG seeks to be an avenue of development in its stated goal of promoting free and open source software - from its technical superiority to ultimately the freedom it gives to everyone. To date, PLUG has about 800 registered users in its mailing list.</p>\r\n<p>The PLUG is the largest community of Linux enthusiasts, developers and advocates in the Philippines. It regularly conducts free quarterly technical seminars as part of its mission to meet the needs of the Linux community. It also holds technical forums and manages several mailing lists including one for Linux beginners.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Vision</h2>\r\n<p>Advocate the use of Linux.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Mission</h2>\r\n<p>Provide for the needs of the Linux community and the general public in furtherance of the Vision goals. Cooperate with and coordinate among various sectors (research, education, corporate, government, non-profit, etc.) in assisting the community (users and non-users alike). Educate and empower members so that they will be self-sustaining and self-motivating contributors to the Organization\'s success.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Roles</h2>\r\n<p>Establish Special Interest Groups to further develop specific technical, policy and/or social issues, according to each members\' interests and capability to contribute and learn. Promote Linux and Open Source through electronic (web, mailing lists) and traditional media, as well as via personal interaction (meetings, seminars).</p>', '', '1', '10', '2013-09-28 14:19:53', '168', '', '2013-10-12 13:16:10', '168', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-09-28 14:19:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"0\",\"link_titles\":\"0\",\"show_tags\":\"0\",\"show_intro\":\"0\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"0\",\"link_category\":\"0\",\"show_parent_category\":\"0\",\"link_parent_category\":\"0\",\"show_author\":\"0\",\"link_author\":\"0\",\"show_create_date\":\"0\",\"show_modify_date\":\"0\",\"show_publish_date\":\"0\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"0\",\"show_icons\":\"0\",\"show_print_icon\":\"0\",\"show_email_icon\":\"0\",\"show_vote\":\"0\",\"show_hits\":\"0\",\"show_noauth\":\"0\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', '7', '2', '', '', '1', '539', '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', '1', '*', ''), ('8', '48', 'Constitution of The Philippine Linux Users\' Group, Inc.', 'constitution', '<h2>I. Name</h2>\r\n<p>The organization shall be known as the Philippine Linux Users\' Group, and shall be referred in this constitution as PLUG.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>II. Emblem</h2>\r\n<p>The official emblem, which shall be used for all official transactions and documents of PLUG, shall be as detailed below:</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>III. Aims and Purposes</h2>\r\n<p>PLUG shall strive to fulfill its purpose, which are encompassed in the following tenets:</p>\r\n<h3>1. Vision</h3>\r\n<p>To be an enabler of human progress in the global society, starting with the Philippines, by vigilantly advocating the use of Linux and Open Source Software, so as to reflect positively on both the product, its creators, developers, and users.</p>\r\n<h3>2.Mission</h3>\r\n<p>Provide for the needs of the Linux community and the general public in furtherance of the Vision goals. Cooperate with and coordinate among various sectors (research, education, corporate, government, non-profit, etc.) in assisting the community (Users and non-Users alike.) Educate and empower members so that they will be self-sustaining and self-motivating contributors to the Organization\'s success.</p>\r\n<h3>3. Roles</h3>\r\n<p>Establish Special Interest Groups to further develop specific technical, policy and/or social issues, according to each members\' interests and capability to contribute and learn. Promote Linux and Open Source through electronic (web, mailing lists) and traditional media, as well as via personal interaction (meetings, seminars).</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>IV. Composition and Nature</h2>\r\n<p>PLUG shall not be used for the advancement of partisan commercial, religious, political, idealogical or ethnic issues.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>V. Membership</h2>\r\n<p>Any person, whether an individual or juridical, can be apply and maintain membership provided that the person passes the following qualifications:</p>\r\n<p>1. Individual members must be willing to abide to the constitution and all legal laws promulgated by PLUG. They must also exhibit verifiable willingness to become members of PLUG and interest in the further advancement of open source.</p>\r\n<p>2. Juridical members must be willing to abide to the constitution and all legal laws promulgated by PLUG. They must also exhibit verifiable willingness to become members of PLUG and must have conducted a free open source-related project and/or activity prior to application for membership.</p>\r\n<p>Individual and juridical members shall be required to pay reasonable membership fees as deemed appropriate as well as present at least two valid IDs.</p>\r\n<p>A membership for one fiscal year shall be granted for qualified persons; after which the said membership status can be renewed by the member at his own discretion granted he passes the qualifications for membership.</p>\r\n<p>To be considered in good standing, a member must not have outstanding financial obligations and/or other liabilities to the organization upon the time that such requirement would be checked as well as abide by all existing regulations and by-laws of PLUG.</p>\r\n<p>A special committee shall be formed by the president consisting of appointed members which shall take charge of qualifying members and applicants.</p>\r\n<p>New applicants seeking membership to PLUG must be qualified for membership using the criteria stated above, and must be sponsored by two members in good standing as a means for ascertaining that such a person exists.</p>\r\n<p>Violations of the provisions of this constitution and promulgated regulations shall be considered as grounds for revocation or denial of granting membership.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>VI. Meetings</h2>\r\n<p>Meetings conducted by PLUG shall be classified as either one of the following:</p>\r\n<p>1. Special meetings shall be convened upon the call of the president.</p>\r\n<p>2. Regular meetings shall be convened as determined by the board and shall be included in the roster of PLUG\'s activities for the year.</p>\r\n<p>3. Board meetings shall involve the convening of PLUG\'s board of directors for official PLUG business.</p>\r\n<p>4. General assembly.</p>\r\n<p> An annual general assembly which shall consist of members of PLUG shall be called on the 2nd Saturday of October. Such shall be called for the purpose of electing eleven (11) members in good standing which shall form the composition of the new board of directors for the incoming fiscal year. The incumbent president or the next highest elected officer in line must be present during the conduct of the general assembly.</p>\r\n<p> Nominations for board members shall be conducted a month prior to the general assembly. Such nominations shall be done in the PLUG mailing list and shall culminate two (2) weeks after.</p>\r\n<p> Nominations shall be based on the qualifications of the person/s wished to be nominated. A nominee shall (i) have been a member of PLUG for at least one year, (ii) be of good moral character, and (iii) have relevant experience in the position for which s/he is<br />being nominated.</p>\r\n<p> All members, whether individual or juridical are entitled to cast one (1) vote during general assemblies. Only members in good standing shall be eligible to vote.</p>\r\n<p> Votes can be cast using email sent at the PLUG mailing list, of which format shall be prescribed by the board of directors, before the conduct of the general assembly as well as during the proceedings of the general assembly wherein the gathering of votes shall be culminated. However, should a member  who previously cast his vote in a mechanism outside the proceedings of the general assembly  choose to attend the election to be held in the general assembly nonetheless, his previous vote shall be nullified in favor of the vote that he will cast during the proceedings of the election during the general assembly.</p>\r\n<p> Members can send a proxy to cast their votes provided that the proxy can produce evidence of the member\'s consent through means mutually acceptable to both parties.</p>\r\n<p>All notifications for meetings should be done at least one week before the date of meeting. Notifications for the General Assembly must be done at least one month before the date of meeting.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>VII. Officers and Directors</h2>\r\n<p>The members of the board of directors shall convene to elect within themselves the following positions which shall be considered as elected officers:</p>\r\n<p>1. President</p>\r\n<p> He shall be in charge of general management of the activities of the organization.</p>\r\n<p>2. Vice President  Internal / Secretariat</p>\r\n<p> He shall be in charge of the smooth conduct of the organization\' internal affairs. He shall be the officer responsible for the proper dissemination of information and activities of interest to PLUG to all recognized members.</p>\r\n<p> He shall supervise directly the membership committee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Vice President  External / Public Relations</p>\r\n<p> He shall be in charge of public relations activities that would be conducted and sanctioned by PLUG as official activities and/or promotions. He shall be the chief liaison officer of PLUG to other external organizations.</p>\r\n<p> He shall supervise directly the advocacy committee.</p>\r\n<p>4. Treasurer</p>\r\n<p> He shall be in charge of the proper management of the organization\'s liquid and other assets, as well as the proper disbursement of funds. The fund shall be deposited in a corporate account in a bank designated by the Board.</p>\r\n<p> He shall be accountable for the maintenance of the organization\'s funds as well as the appropriate accompanying records as prescribed by law and standard operating procedures of PLUG.</p>\r\n<p>5. Internal Auditor</p>\r\n<p> He shall ensure the transparency of all transactions by means of checking all accounts and transactions conducted by the organization.</p>\r\n<p>The treasurer and auditor positions cannot be occupied simultaneously by board members that hail from a single company.</p>\r\n<p>In the event that an elected position be vacated by events such as resignation, disqualification from the organization, death, or inability of the officer to effectively discharge the duties and responsibilities accorded to the position, the board shall reconvene and elect among themselves a replacement.</p>\r\n<p>The president shall have the prerogative of appointing PLUG members outside the composition of the elective positions. Such members appointed to perform official transactions in behalf of PLUG which shall be considered as appointed officers. The following positions shall comprise the roster of appointed positions but shall not be restricted to such:</p>\r\n<p>1. Secretary</p>\r\n<p>S/he shall be the custodian of all official seals and records of the meetings of the Board and the assembly. S/he shall affix signatures and official seal of the organization on all official papers.</p>\r\n<p>S/he shall maintain the membership roster which is his/her basis for calling the membership roll during the PLUG assembly meetings.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>VIII. Board of Directors</h2>\r\n<p>The board of directors shall be composed of eleven (11) members of good standing which shall be elected from the body of PLUG members during the election held during the annual general assembly. The board shall be the governing body of the organization.</p>\r\n<p>The board of directors shall be elected during the general assembly on the 2nd week of October and shall serve for one (1) fiscal year. The newly elected board shall effectively start their term of service on the 1st week of December after a two-month transition from the outgoing board of directors of the previous fiscal year, and shall end on the 1st week of December of the next year.</p>\r\n<p>The board shall be tasked with the planning, establishment and enforcement of all laws, policies and activities that PLUG will undertake. They shall also exert general supervision and control over all funds accessible to the organization.</p>\r\n<p>The board shall also be the sole authority that can declare a project to be an authorized activity sanctioned by the organization. Authorized activities must be beneficial to the organization as well as approved by the board.</p>\r\n<p>Should there be vacancies in the the board of directors replacements shall be appointed by the remaining members of the board through a majority vote. The appointed board member shall have voting privileges in the board but shall not be eligible for any elected position.</p>\r\n<p>In the event that the entire board of directors be vacated, the remaining members of PLUG shall reconvene via a general assembly to elect new board members to replace the vacated board in the manner prescribed for elections during general assemblies.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>IX. Standing Committees</h2>\r\n<p>The following are the list of standing committees:</p>\r\n<p>1.Membership</p>\r\n<p>The membership and information committee shall be in-charge of screening applicants for membership to the organization as well as evaluating current members. This committee shall be supervised by the VP-Internal. Membership of this committee shall be open to all members in good standing.</p>\r\n<p>2. Advocacy</p>\r\n<p>The advocacy committee shall be in-charge of promoting the organization\'s advocacies based on the mission and vision. This committee shall be supervised by the VP-External. Membership of this committee shall be open to all members in good standing.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>X. Special Committees</h2>\r\n<p>Special committees shall be formed by the board voting in majority as the case may require.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>XI. Amendments</h2>\r\n<p>Amendments to the constitution can be done by members in good standing, and must be sponsored by a member of the board of directors.</p>\r\n<p>Ratification of amendments shall be done via convening of a general assembly voting in quorum. Quorum shall be defined as at the very least 50% of eligible voters plus one more person. Rules for casting of votes for the proposed amendments shall be the same as the regulations for casting votes for the composition of the board.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>XII. Effectivity</h2>\r\n<p>This constitution shall take effect upon approval of the Board.</p>\r\n<p>The provision of this Constitution shall be prospective in character and nature.</p>', '', '1', '10', '2013-09-28 14:33:53', '168', '', '2013-10-01 05:34:49', '168', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-09-28 14:33:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_in